id: pm-9byd
title: "Expose id_prefix, author_default, output.default_format, locks.ttl_seconds via pm config set"
description: "id_prefix, author_default, output.default_format, and locks.ttl_seconds are listed in CONFIGURATION.md as configurable settings but have no pm config set key. They require manual editing of .agents/pm/settings.json. Adding them to NESTED_SETTING_DESCRIPTORS (the approved pattern for leaf settings) would make them script- and agent-friendly."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,"area:cli","area:config",dx
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:07:49.621Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-17T05:22:46.183Z"
author: audit-cli-schema-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- pm config set id_prefix <prefix> updates id_prefix in settings.json\n- pm config set author_default <name> updates author_default\n- pm config set output_default_format <format> updates output.default_format\n- pm config set locks_ttl_seconds <n> updates locks.ttl_seconds (integer, min 1)\n- pm config get/list shows the new keys\n- CONFIGURATION.md updated with example config set commands\n- Shell completions updated"
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: low
confidence: high
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-17T04:30:02.384Z",claude-code-agent,"Implemented via 4 NestedSettingDescriptor entries in src/core/config/nested-settings.ts (config.ts unchanged - it iterates the table dynamically at L433 and L1164). Entries: {key:id_prefix, path:id_prefix, kind:string, non_empty:true}; {key:author_default, path:author_default, kind:string, non_empty:true}; {key:output_default_format, path:output.default_format, kind:string, choices:[toon,json]}; {key:locks_ttl_seconds, path:locks.ttl_seconds, kind:integer, min:1}. SURPRISE: body guessed output.default_format choices were json/human; actual is toon/json per PmSettings types.ts:648 and validator vLiteral(toon,json) settings-validator.ts:390. Paths honored by validator: id_prefix=vString L386, author_default=vString L387, locks.ttl_seconds=vNumber int L389, output.default_format=vLiteral L390. Tests: extended tests/unit/commands/config-key-aliases-search.spec.ts (new general-setting aliases describe: path map, kebab/snake resolve, set/get round-trip, accept+reject for each). completion.ts needs NO entry (nested keys not statically listed). typecheck clean; config specs 106 green."
close_reason: "Added: pm config set now supports id_prefix, author_default, output_default_format, locks_ttl_seconds via NESTED_SETTING_DESCRIPTORS (script/agent friendly, no hand-editing settings.json)."
body: "## Context\n\nCONFIGURATION.md lines 59-63 document id_prefix, author_default, output.default_format, and locks.ttl_seconds as user-facing settings.\nNone appear in CONFIG_KEY_VALUES (src/cli/commands/config.ts:44-92) nor in NESTED_SETTING_DESCRIPTORS (src/core/config/nested-settings.ts).\nThe established pattern for adding leaf settings is to add a NestedSettingDescriptor entry — adding them requires no other code changes per the module's JSDoc.\nNested-settings path for each:\n  id_prefix -> 'id_prefix'\n  author_default -> 'author_default'\n  output.default_format -> 'output.default_format'\n  locks.ttl_seconds -> 'locks.ttl_seconds'\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- pm config set id_prefix <prefix> updates id_prefix in settings.json\n- pm config set author_default <name> updates author_default\n- pm config set output_default_format <format> updates output.default_format\n- pm config set locks_ttl_seconds <n> updates locks.ttl_seconds (integer, min 1)\n- pm config get/list shows the new keys\n- CONFIGURATION.md updated with example config set commands\n- Shell completions updated\n\n## Evidence\n\n- docs/CONFIGURATION.md:59-63 (mentions but no config set examples for these keys)\n- src/cli/commands/config.ts:44-92 (CONFIG_KEY_VALUES — none of the 4 keys present)\n- src/core/config/nested-settings.ts (NESTED_SETTING_DESCRIPTORS — none of the 4 keys present)\n- src/core/config/nested-settings.ts:25-48 (NestedSettingDescriptor pattern for new additions)"
